    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed at MRL 5 (required level 5); all achieved levels meet or exceed required levels. Validation metric W = 0.87 exceeds 0.80 threshold. GCI on primary QoI (HI) is 1.8%, well within 5% acceptance criterion. Sobol sensitivity analysis identifies dominant uncertainty sources (hemolysis model exponent alpha, tip clearance) and confirms 95th-percentile HI remains below RH < 1 acceptance criterion across all operating points. Independent reproduction confirms use error is controlled. Model form uncertainty quantified at ±18% on HI; combined with measurement uncertainty, 95th-percentile RH = 0.91 < 1.0. Equivalency assessment confirms validation activities cover 94% of COU operating space. All evidence traceable to archived datasets, instrumentation calibration records, and peer-reviewed methods. The credibility body of evidence is judged sufficient to support the regulatory decision at MRL 5.",
